1. What happens when you initialize a repository? Why do you need to do it?

   a .git directory is created and populated. git init is required to create the .git structure
   so that file commits can be tracked and stored and the repositroy can be managed.

2. How is the staging area different from the working directory and the repository? What value do 
   you think it offers?

   The staging area is a temporary space for files that are to be comitted to the repository. Files
   may be added and reomved prior to executing a commit.

